m_q.target_metric: Count of modern cities with population > 100k within 0.1 degrees of any ancient Roman city
filters: distance between worldcities (lat, lng) and roman_cities (Latitude (Y), Longitude (X)) <= 0.1 degrees
sub_questions: Calculate the distance between each modern city and each ancient Roman city.
Filter modern cities with population greater than 100,000.
Identify modern cities within 0.1 degrees of any ancient Roman city.
Count the number of modern cities that meet the criteria.

constraints: Distance calculation must use appropriate formula (e.g., Haversine) for spherical coordinates.
Ensure consistent coordinate systems (WGS84) for both datasets.
